<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880519-0141 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News: Hughes Supply Declares Split, Increases Dividend </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HUG </CO><IN> DIV </IN><DATELINE> ORLANDO, Fla.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hughes Supply Inc. said its board declared a 3-for-2 stock split and raised its quarterly dividend to eight cents a share from 7.3 cents, adjusted for the split.    Hughes, a wholesale distributor of electrical, plumbing and utility supplies, said the split will be paid June 15 to stock of record June 1, boosting total shares outstanding to 4,858,537 from 3,239,025. It said the quarterly cash dividend will be paid Aug. 19 to stock of record Aug. 5.    Separately, Hughes said its board adopted a shareholder rights plan designed, among other things, to discourage any takeover bids that aren't cleared first by the company's directors. </TEXT></DOC>